(158, 1, '2016-10-19 21:39:02', '2016-10-19 16:09:02', '<h2>Reflexology</h2>\r\nReflexology is the practice of applying pressure techniques to the feet and hands. When these techniques are applied in a systematic manner to reflex areas on the feet or hands, they can have a positive impact on the related areas of the body and health concerns. In addition to addressing health concerns, however, reflexology can set your body free from the stresses it experiences throughout the day as well as make your feet feel good.\r\n\r\nWhether youâre seeking a treat or a treatment, luxuriating in relaxation or addressing your health concerns, reflexology can help. By choosing to use reflexology, you take a step on your journey to well-being. Wellness is literally in your hands.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"Refelxology\" class=\"ow-button-hover\" title=\"Refelxology\" href=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/refelxology/\">\r\n\r\n\r\nRead More\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/refelxology/\"> <img class=\"so-widget-image\" title=\"Reflexology\" src=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/maxresdefault-300x210.jpg\" srcset=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/maxresdefault-300x210.jpg 300w, http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/maxresdefault.jpg 600w\" alt=\"Reflexology\" width=\"300\" height=\"210\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<h2 class=\"entry-title\">Dorn Therapy</h2>\r\nThe Dorn method is a form of manual, holistic alternative therapy claimed to be used to correct misalignments in the spinal column and other joints The Dorn method is a form of manual, holistic alternative therapy claimed to be used to correct misalignments in the spinal column and other joints. In its theoretical approach, it is somewhat[vague] related to chiropractic and osteopathy, although it is different in its practical application. It was developed in the 1970s by the German lay-healer Dieter Dorn.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"Refelxology\" class=\"ow-button-hover\" title=\"Refelxology\" href=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/dorn-therapy/\">\r\n\r\n\r\nRead More\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/dorn-therapy/\"> <img class=\"so-widget-image\" title=\"Dorn Therapy\" src=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dorn4-300x210.jpg\" srcset=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dorn4-300x210.jpg 300w, http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dorn4.jpg 600w\" alt=\"Dorn Therapy\" width=\"300\" height=\"210\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<h2 class=\"entry-title\">Cupping Therapy</h2>\r\nCupping therapy is an ancient form of alternative medicine in which a therapist puts special cups on your skin for a few minutes to create suction. People get it for many purposes, including to help with pain, inflammation, blood flow, relaxation and well-being, and as a type of deep-tissue massage.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"Refelxology\" class=\"ow-button-hover\" title=\"Refelxology\" href=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/cupping-therapy/\">\r\n\r\n\r\nRead More\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/cupping-therapy/\"> <img class=\"so-widget-image\" title=\"Cupping Therapy\" src=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cups.jpg\" srcset=\"http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cups.jpg 600w, http://www.divinesreflexology.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cups-300x210.jpg 300w\" alt=\"Cupping Therapy\" width=\"600\" height=\"420\" />\r\n</a>', 'Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'services', '', '', '2017-01-18 00:54:28', '2017-01-17 19:24:28', '', 0, 'http://www.divinesreflexology.com/?page_id=158', 0, 'page', '', 0),
